Note.Content: RSV "fountain" NIV "spring" NJB "well-spring" | NJPS NRSV "abode" REB "dwells" GNT CEV "live" ESV "lived" = עון

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: = one of two parts of the body of humans and animals that is used to see things, after which the observed information is stored and processed in the mind; sparkling when the body is healthy and strong, but dim when weak or sick; the eyes also play a significant role in determining whether a person is considered beautiful or not; eyes can reflect both an attitude of compassion and a sentiment of malice; ≈ high eyes are associated with pride, whereas lowly eyes are connected with humility; a good eye is associated with generosity, whereas an evil eye denotes stinginess; winking the eye is associated with underhanded practices
= the hair growing on the ridge above a person’s eye socket
= folds of skin which cover the eye when it is closed
literally: the eye (of an object); hence: = the part of an object that can be seen with the eye
= hole in the earth that gives access to the subterranean water which either comes to the surface or can be drawn from it
= town; ◄ territory of {L:Judah<SDBH:יְהוּדָה>}; ► assigned to clan of {L:Aaron<SDBH:אַהֲרֹן>}, tribe of {L:Levi<SDBH:לֵוִי>}
